{{Quick Guide}}

==Details==
{{Quest details page|Dragon Slayer I}}

==Walkthrough==
===Beginning===
'''Recommended:''' ''[[Chronicle]] or [[combat bracelet]] (members) with at least 2 charges, [[amulet of glory]] (members) with at least 1 charge, Lumbridge teleport (if you need [[anti-dragon shield]])''

{{Checklist|
*Talk to [[Guildmaster]] in [[Champions' Guild]]. {{Chat option|2Can I have a quest?|1 Start Dragon Slayer Quest?}}
*Talk to [[Oziach]] in [[Edgeville]]. {{Chat option|1Can you sell me a rune platebody?|1The Guildmaster of the Champions' Guild told me.|1I thought you were going to give me a quest.|1A dragon, that sounds like fun.}}
*Talk to Guildmaster in Champions' Guild. Make sure you get the maze key by asking about Melzar's map piece, and also ask about Thalzar and Lozar's map pieces as well as where to find the right ship. {{Chat option|2I talked to Oziach...|1How can I find the route to Crandor?|1Where is Melzar's map piece?|1Where is Thalzar's map piece?|2Where is Lozar's map piece?|3Where can I find the right ship?|2How can I protect myself from the dragon's breath?|3Okay, I'll get going!}}
*If you don't already have an [[anti-dragon shield]], speak to [[Duke Horacio]]. {{Chat option|1I seek a shield that will protect me from dragonbreath.|1Elvarg, the dragon of Crandor island!|1Yes|2So, are you going to give me the shield or not?}}
}}

===Map pieces===
{{Checklist|
*Map pieces can be obtained in any order.
*After obtaining all 3, combine them by using them on each other.
}}

====Thalzar's map piece====
'''Items required:''' ''[[Silk]], [[lobster pot]], [[unfired bowl]], and [[Wizard's mind bomb]]''

{{Checklist|
*Talk to [[Oracle]] on [[Ice Mountain]]. Make sure you have talked to the [[Guildmaster]] about where the Thalzar's map piece is. {{Chat option|1I seek a piece of the map to the island of Crandor.}}
*Enter the [[Dwarven mine]] and '''use''' [[silk]], [[lobster pot]], [[unfired bowl]], (make sure to right click) [[wizard's mind bomb]] on the [[magic door]] at the northeast side of the mine. You should automatically enter the door.
*Enter the magic door, open the chest, and '''search''' the chest to receive a map piece. Press space or ensure that you finish the dialogue. (Re-entry doesn't require the re-use of the items if you make a mistake.)
}}

====Melzar's map piece====
'''Items required:''' ''[[Maze key]], weapon, armour, food, and potions to defeat lvl 82 [[Lesser demon]]''
[[File:Melzar's Maze map.png|thumb|A map of the maze]]
{{Checklist|
*Once you've gotten the Maze key from the [[Guildmaster]] head to [[Rimmington]].
*Enter [[Melzar's Maze]].
*Kill the small [[zombie rat]] with a long tail to get the key and enter the north-western door and climb up the ladder.
*Kill the [[Ghost (Melzar's Maze)|ghost]] wearing a hood, a tube top, and no cape to get the key and enter the second door from the north on the eastern wall and climb up the ladder.
*Kill the [[Skeleton (Melzar's Maze)|skeleton]] with the round shield to get the key and enter the westmost door on the southern wall and climb down the ladder 3 times.
*Kill the [[Zombie (Melzar's Maze)|zombies]] to get the key and enter the blue door.
*Kill [[Melzar the Mad]] to get the key and enter the purple (magenta) door.
*Kill the [[Lesser demon (Melzar's Maze)|lesser demon]] to get the key and enter the green door. (Can be safespotted by luring him to the magenta door)
*Open and search the chest to receive a map piece.
}}

====Lozar's map piece====
'''Items required:'''  ''Ranged/magic/halberd and telegrab runes to kill Wormbrain or 10,000 coins''{{Checklist|
*Go to the jail in [[Port Sarim]].
*Either kill [[Wormbrain]] with ranged/magic/halberd and [[telegrab]] the map piece or pay him 10,000 [[coins]] for it. Make sure you have talked to the [[Guildmaster]] about where the Lozar's map piece is. {{Chat option|1I believe you've got a piece of map that I need.|3I suppose I could pay you for the map piece...|2Alright then, 10,000 it is.}}
}}

===Obtaining a boat===
'''Items required:''' ''Hammer, 3 [[planks]], 90 [[steel nails]], 2,000 coins,'' [[Crandor map]]''.'' '''Recommended:''' ''[[Amulet of glory]] (members) with at least 1 charge for teleport to [[Draynor Village]]''

{{Checklist|
*Grab 3 wood planks, 90 steel nails, a hammer, and 2,000 coins out of the bank.
*Talk to [[Klarense]] in the southern docks of [[Port Sarim]] by the Void Outpost boat and pay him 2,000 coins. {{Chat option|4I'd like to buy her.|1Yep, sounds good.}}
*Go on board, climb down the ladder and repair the hole 3 times.
*Talk to [[Ned]] in [[Draynor]] with the map in your inventory. {{Chat option|1You're a sailor? Could you take me to Crandor?}}
}}

===The fight===
'''Items required:''' ''[[Anti-dragon shield]], weapon, armour, food, and potions to defeat [[Elvarg]].'' '''Recommended:''' ''Antifire potion (members), [[amulet of glory]] (members) with at least 1 charge to teleport to [[Edgeville]].''

{{Checklist|'''{{Colour|red|Warning}}:''' if you leave Elvarg's cave for any reason you will need planks and nails again to re-repair the ship; however, if you complete the optional task of opening the wall south of Elvarg's cave, you will gain access to the lair easily through the Karamja volcano dungeon and without the need to travel to Crandor again.
*Prepare for the fight. Make sure you have your [[Antifire potion]] and [[Anti-dragon shield]] with you.
*Return to the [[Lady_Lumbridge|boat]] you previously repaired in [[Port Sarim]]. Board the ship and talk to Captain [[Ned]]. {{Chat option|1Yep, sounds good.}}
*Climb on top of the volcano and enter the hole.  (After the cutscene climb back out of the hole for a Karamja medium task.)
**''(Optional)'' Before teleporting out, head south from Elvarg's cave and open the wall to unlock another Karamja medium task.
*Head south and kill [[Elvarg]]. Depending on your level, you may [[flinch]] [[Elvarg]] in the southeast corner of her cave for a long, but safe fight. You will automatically collect her head as proof of your victory.

}}

===Finishing up===
{{Checklist|
*Talk to [[Oziach]] in [[Edgeville]].}}

'''Quest complete!'''

